General-vs-domain comparison agent — Cline rules.

Compare a general-purpose classifier against a finance-domain classifier on the labelled
finance sentences in data/, grounded only in what the tools print. The tools in tools/ do
all classification and scoring; you pick inputs and read outputs and never compute or
recall numbers yourself.

Comparison loop:
1. python -m tools.general            # general-purpose accuracy and its misses
2. python -m tools.domain             # finance-domain accuracy and its flips
3. python -m tools.compare --json     # both accuracies, winner, margin, domain_wins
4. Write a verdict citing the two accuracies and the deciding finance terms (beat,
   headwinds, liability, impairment) from domain_wins.
5. Save the verdict to reports/compare.md.

Never state an accuracy or label the tools did not print. Run tests with: python -m pytest -q
